ABUJA – Nigeria and Israel are to strengthen bilateral ties in the areas of Science, Technology and Innovation(STI) for socio-economic development of both countries. Dr. Ogbonnaya Onu made this known on Tuesday in Abuja, when he received the new Ambassador of the State of Israel to Nigeria, Michael Freeman, in his office. Onu informed the newly appointed Israeli envoy of the desire of Nigeria to diversify her economy and build a knowledge-based economy. APC Chairmanship: Stakeholders Kick Against Sen Adamu, Nnamani Ekiti 2022: Segun Oni Storms Ekiti With SDP Flag, Urges Ekiti To… He said; “Nigeria is blessed with natural resources and we have some of the most intelligent people in the world.. “We want to diversify our economy, because we believe with the huge human capital, we can add value to our raw materials and create jobs for our youths.” The minister who praised the historical diplomatic ties between both nations, added that the relationship has yielded positive results over the years. He therefore, congratulated the new Ambassador on his appointment and urged him to build upon the successes of his predecessors. Earlier, the Israeli Ambassador,  Amb. Michael Freeman, said his country was willing to collaborate with Nigeria on many socio-economic areas, especially challenges that can be solved using Science, Technology and Innovation.